claim.claim-text:
3. A pivot pin assembly for a pivot joint of a work vehicle comprising:
a metal cylinder, said cylinder having a first end and a second end, said first end having a circumferential groove with at least one blocked portion;
a retaining plate having a first edge disposed in said circumferential groove;
wherein the at least one blocked portion includes first and second blocked portions;
wherein the first and second blocked portions are disposed about 180 degrees apart;
wherein the first and second blocked portions subdivide the circumferential groove into a first arcuate portion and a second arcuate portion, wherein each of said first and second arcuate portions have substantially equal length; wherein the groove defines a flange, and further wherein portions of the flange recessed into the first and second blocked portions of the groove have a finish indicating that the first and second blocked portions were formed by pressing or stamping the flange.
